rategic bulwark. Yet Manzikert was not a disaster. This book examines the geopolitical background and the origins of the campaign that led to the battle, the main protagonists, and their strategies and battle tactics. It also evaluates the primary sources and the enduring legacy of the battle, for both the Greek and Turkish historiography of the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aManzikert, Battle of, Turkey, 1071. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aAsia Minor, Romanos Diogenes.  aByzantium.  aSeljuk Turks.  amedieval war.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781802701722?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781802701722423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781802701722/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles